post_text:
We are so EXCITED!!!

For the first time since we released at noon on March 13, we will have students back in the classroom. It is so hard to believe it has been over five months since this has happened.

A few reminders about this new school year.

* Gates Open at 7:35 am

* School Starts at 7:55 am

* ALL students need to have a mask. Grades 3-8 are required to wear them thoughout the day. The younger grades, at certain times, like pick-up, will also be required to wear them.

* ALL students need to bring a water bottle. Students will not be allowed to use water fountains. Procedures are in place for students to refill them if need be.

* Visitors are not allowed on campus. If a parent needs to come to campus, they MUST come to the office.

* Exception this week --- ONLY PK & K parents will be allowed to walk their child to the classroom these first three days. Parents must wear masks.

Again, we are so EXCITED to have our students back and to SAFELY "kick off" this new school year!!!

See You Tomorrow!

post_text:
Good morning SHISD Cougar families:

It is hard to believe that we are already in the month of August. As it is every year at this time, the beginning of school is at the forefront for all. That is most definitely the case this year as school approaches. With that said, I imagine many of you have questions on how school will look this year.

I want to try to ease any anxiety you may have. If you have any questions or concerns about this upcoming school year, please email them to me at swagner@sweethomeisd.org.

I will compile a list and answer the questions to the best of my abilities. I will then post the Q&A so all can see.

Thank You!

post_text:
Sweet Home Cougar Families:

My plan has always been to start school on our original start date of Thursday, August 13. Well, with everything that TEA is having districts do, it has become necessary to push back this start date. Our main priority is the safety and education of all our students. Moving this start date will help accomplish this.

OUR NEW START DATE WILL BE...
WEDNESDAY, AUGUST 19.

I will post the new 2020-2021 school calendar once it is adopted at the next board meeting. But as of right now, I just wanted to inform everyone of this new start date.

Thank You!

post_text:
Revised SHISD 2020-2021 School Calendar:

There are no major changes at this time. But here are the changes approved at the Board Meeting last week...

1. Due to our morning procedures changing, our starting time will now be 7:55. We accomplished a couple of things by starting five minutes earlier. First, students will be going to the classroom instead of the gym. Since they will already be in the classroom, it just made since to gain an extra five minutes. Second, by adding these five minutes, almost a complete two days worth of minutes were added to our calendar. In case there is a closure, these extra minutes will become very important.

2. The commissioner wanted each school district to have at least 10 days built into the calendar in case there is any type of closure. In order to accomplish this, we added some Bad Weather/School Closure days. These days are...
January 5, February 19, February 22, and May 28.

As of right now, these are the only calendar changes that are planned.

post_text:
I know some parents probably have a lot of questions about this coming school year. When will it start? What will it look like? etc, etc, etc, etc...

I also have some of these same questions. But with that said, as of right now, SHISD plans on starting school as planned on Thursday, August 13. And we plan on having in-room classes as normal. This is the plan.

I will continue to monitor guidlines from both the governor and TEA. If changes are necessary, SHISD will make those changes. And when/if these changes are made, I will be sure to communicate this to the parents as soon as possible.

In the meantime, enjoy the rest of your summer and Stay Safe!

Hello Incoming 8th Grade Students and Parents,

I’m excited to announce that I’m leading a trip to Washington D.C. next summer! This trip is going to be so much fun. If you would like to attend the trip I will be hosting a virtual information meeting so that you can ask any questions that you may have, as well as get pricing information, trip dates, and itinerary possibilities. This trip is an incredible opportunity for students to see our nation’s capital!

I will be posting the Zoom login information on the 8th Grade Washington DC Trip 2021 Facebook page. Please feel free to text me or email me for the login information as well, at the number and email address below, if you don’t have Facebook!
I can’t wait to see you and your families at our virtual meeting on Thursday, June 11, at 6 PM.

Ms. Ashley Helweg
Cuero
Program Leader
ahelweg@cueroisd.org
(361) 772-0810

P.S.: Spread the word! Every student going into the 8th grade is invited so please share this with all your friends.

As we continue our long distance learning, I realize that internet access may be difficult to impossible for some families. With that in mind, Sweet Home ISD now has a community WiFi set up.

Anyone can come into our parking lot and connect to the WiFi. You will connect to the network called SHISD-Outside. When you are asked to enter a password, enter Sweet Home.

I hope this makes things a little easier for those with internet difficulties.

As always, Stay Safe!

post_text:
Good Monday morning...I hope everyone is doing fine and staying safe.

I just wanted to remind everyone that there will be no packet pick-up this Thursday. All assignments will be posted on the teacher's webpage which can be found on our school's website. All new assignments should be posted by Thursday.

Most, if not all, assignments do not have to be printed out at home. All students should have to do is open up the assignment and work any problems on loose leaf paper. Then a picture can be taken of the work, then texted or emailed back to the teacher. Each teacher should communicate how they want to receive any work back.

If you have any questions or concerns, please let your teacher or myself know.

Thanks and Stay Safe!
